name: eucalyptus seedling production, in heated greenhouse | eucalyptus seedling, for planting | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/20184/documentation

The dataset refers to the production of 1000 Eucalyptus seedling. The dataset contains the production of Eucalyptus seedlings in a tree nursery for plantation in forests. The seedlings are produced in a heated greenhouse and wood wastes are bought for that. The final product is the seedlings planted in the substrate (as showed in the following picture) inside the polytubes where they are cultivated. Yield capacity is 1.3 million seedlings per month.;Source: EMBRAPA CNPTIA <http://www.agencia.cnptia.embrapa.br/gestor/eucalipto/arvore/CONTAG01_37_2572006132315.html>, access 02 mar 2016.;Polypropylene tubes with substrate are used to the cultivation and it can be reused for 6 to 8 years. However, the consumption of substrate is not included. The production steps are the following:;Source: USP <http://www.teses.usp.br/teses/disponiveis/88/88131/tde-31072012-121351/en.php>, access 02 mar 2016.;As data is from a LCA of MDP board production in Brazil, the original numbers had to be converted using the following information: kg of wood produce per seedling = 74.3 and kg of wood consumed to produce 1 m³ of MDP board = 687.

This activity covers the water, fertilizers and pesticides consumed for cultivation of the seedlings, besides covers the transport of inputs inside the nursery by tractors and the electricity and wood wastes consumption to heat up the greenhouses. 

The activity ends with the seedlings ready to expedition. It does not includes the substrate and package boxes as source does not provide this information.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/013:Plant propagation/0130:Plant propagation

processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The majority of data came from a published source "Life cycle assessment of medium density particleboard (MDP) produced in Brazil" (Silva et al., 2013). Additional and necessary data were collected in the literature.

exchanges.description:
Exchange results from wood chips burning inside the greenhouse.
Emissions from combustion of wood chips were based on USLCI "wood waste, unspecified, combusted in industrial boiler" that considers 50% of moisture content in wood chips and 350 kg/m³ to basic density. The energy efficiency is around 85%.

exchanges.description: Total amount of active substance/s of fertilisers needed for the production of 'eucalyptus seedling, for planting' is calculated to be circa 3.22E-01 kg. Fertiliser/s used in this dataset is/are: 'ammonium sulfate, as N', 'phosphate fertiliser, as P2O5', 'potassium chloride, as K2O'. The total amount of active substance/s is doubled in order to account for the packaging of the dilluted product of fertiliser/s that is/are applied. Therefore, 6.44E-01 kg of packaging for fertilisers is justified with this exchange.
